      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While high doses of vitamin D may help boost the immune system, taking 50,000 IU per day is extremely high and not generally recommended. Taking such a large dose for an extended period may increase the risk of toxicity, causing symptoms like nausea, vomiting, and muscle weakness. The recommended daily intake of vitamin D is typically around 600-800 IU, and most health organizations advise against doses above 4,000 IU per day. Instead, consider consulting with a healthcare professional about the best vitamin D plan for your specific needs.",
